# Track `.cursor/` in git

`.cursor/` at the **repo root** must be versioned. This is NOT the user-level `%USERPROFILE%\.cursor\` / `~/.cursor/` — never add that to the repo.

## Before any commit or push — MUST

1. Check: `git check-ignore -v .cursor .cursor/rules`.
2. If `.gitignore` has a blanket ignore (`.cursor/`, `.cursor/*`, `.cursor/**`), remove it. You may keep targeted ignores for genuinely local-only state (e.g. `.cursor/agent-transcripts/`). Do **not** ignore `.cursor/.local-auto-push` — it is a shared project-level marker (see `local-auto-push-current-branch.mdc`).
3. `git add .cursor/`. Confirm `git status` shows the intended changes.

## You MUST NOT

- Push only part of `.cursor/` without explicit user request.
- Commit secrets (e.g. tokens in `mcp.json`) under `.cursor/`. Use env vars or untracked local files.
- Add the user-level `~/.cursor/` into the project repo.
